Package: climbeR
Title: Calculate Minimal Maximal Subtree Depth for Ranger Package Trees
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: c(person("John", "Karlen", email = "jkarlen@massmutual.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre")), 
                  person("MassMutual Advanced Analytics", 
                  comment="http://datascience.massmutual.com", role="aut"))
Description: This package calculates first and second order, average minimal
    maximal subtree depth for a forest object, produced by the R Ranger
    package. This variable importance metric is implemented, as described in
    Ishwaran et. al.
    ("High-Dimensional Variable Selection for Survival Data", March 2010)
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.1.0)
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports: 
    ggplot2 (>= 1.0.1)
Suggests: 
    survival (>= 2.38-1),
    ranger,
    knitr,
    rmarkdown
RoxygenNote: 5.0.0
VignetteBuilder: knitr
